I'm working on a neutron shielding evaluation project at the Skandvik Nuclear Research Complex in Malmö. We're testing layered composite materials for use in next-gen portable radiography units. I need help optimizing a Monte Carlo simulation in Geant4 to model neutron flux attenuation through a boron-carbide-polyethylene matrix. The setup is fully contained within our licensed Class II experimental hall, under SSM supervision, and all simulations are required before we proceed to physical prototyping.

